===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|stylus}}, alternative spelling of {{m|la|stilus}}. Unrelated to Ancient Greek {{m|grc|στῦλος||pillar}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK|US}} {{IPA|/ˈstaɪl.əs/|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|aɪləs|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|styli|styluses}}

# A sharp [[stick]] used in ancient times for [[writing]] in clay [[tablet]]s or other surfaces; a sharp tool for [[engraving]].
#* {{quote-journal|lang=en|author=Jane Shilling|title=The Golden Thread: the Story of Writing, by Ewan Clayton, review &#91;print edition: Illuminating language&#93;|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/books/historybookreviews/10304108/The-Golden-Thread-the-Story-of-Writing-by-Ewan-Clayton-review.html|archiveurl=|archivedate=|work={{w|The Daily Telegraph}} (Review)|date=14 September 2013|page=R28|passage=[T]he pleasure of writing on wax with a '''stylus''' is exemplified by the fine, flowing hand of a Roman scribe who made out the birth certificate of Herennia Gemella, born March 128 AD.}}
# A [[phonograph]] [[needle]].
# A small plastic [[stick]] used as a [[pen]] for writing on the touch-sensitive screen of an electronic device.
# A tool for making small dots on a piece of heavy paper, used to produce [[Braille]] writing for the blind by hand.
# {{lb|en|botany}} {{synonym of|style|lang=en}}

